translated:
Lind, Gunnar Olof, prakt, läkare, Göteborg, born on April 13, 1885 in Gothenburg, son of factory worker Sven Magnus L. and Selma Eugenia Gillholm. Married on November 11 with practicing physician Signe Norström. Children: Barbro born in 1912, Kerstin in 1916, Claes Göran in 1920, Sven Arne in 1924. 

Completed secondary education in Gothenburg in 1903, received a Bachelor of Medicine in 1909 and a medical license in 1916 from the Carolina Institute. Assistant and intern physician at Crown Princess Lovisa's Hospital Division of Medicine from 1916-1917, intern physician at S:t Göran's Hospital Division for Lung Tuberculosis in 1918, the same at Flensburg Children's Hospital from 1918-1920, including three months as acting senior physician. Assistant physician at Gothenburg Epidemic Hospital in 1919, medical doctor at Adolfsberg Children's Home from 1920-1935, at Child Protection I in Gothenburg from 1921, at the Milk Drop-in Center in Gothenburg from the same year, at Lundby Children's Home from 1931, at Gothenburg Community Middle School from 1925, and at Gothenburg Public School from 1929. Temporary district physician in Gothenburg for shorter periods from 1928-1932, practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1920. Knight of the Royal Order of Vasa.
